{
  "texts": [
    "Given a BAO A = ⟨A, ∧, -, ⊤, {■ i } i∈I ⟩ and algebraic model M = ⟨A, θ⟩, we define the filter frame A f = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P f ⟩, the general filter frame A g = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P g ⟩, and M g = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, π⟩ as follows:1.",
    "S is the set of proper filters in A;2.",
    "X ⊑ Y iff X ⊇ Y; 3.",
    "XR i Y iff for all x ∈ A, if ■ i x ∈ X then x ∈ Y; 4.",
    "P f = RO(S, ⊑) (recall Notation 2.19); 5. where x = {X ∈ S | x ∈ X}, P g = { x | x ∈ A}; 6. π(p) = {X ∈ S | θ(p) ∈ X}."
  ]
}